<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{3}{y}={75}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{x}+{y}=-{17}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},-{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+-{3}{y}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}={75}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{75}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{\left(\frac{{{75}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}\right)}+{1}{y}=-{17}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{1}}{{-{{6}}}}\cdot{\left({75}\right)}-\frac{{1}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}+{1}{y}=-{17}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{12.5}-{\left(-{0.5}\right)}{y}+{1}{y}=-{17}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.5}{y}+{\left({1}\right)}{y}=-{17}--{12.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.5}{y}+{\left({1}\right)}{y}=-{4.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{0.5}+{\left({1}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{4.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.5}{y}=-{4.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{4.5}}{{0.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+-{3}{\left(-{9}\right)}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{\left({27}\right)}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}={75}-{\left({27}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}={48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{48}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>